programme.title: Wimbledon 2015
programme.desc: Live coverage of the ladies' singles final from the Centre Court at the All England Club, where the Venus Rosewater Dish will be awarded to the winner. Four of the last five finals have been completed in straight sets, and the crowd will be hoping for a lengthy match on the penultimate day of the championships, as the successor to Petra Kvitova is decided. The Czech star was victorious last year against Eugenie Bouchard to add to the crown she won here in 2011 and, starting as the second seed this time, was one of the favourites to be involved this afternoon. Her clash with rising Canadian star Bouchard failed to live up to expectations of a close contest, with the court time of 55 minutes making it the fifth shortest in Wimbledon history. The last final to be decided in a third set was in 2012, when Serena Williams defeated Agnieszka Radwanska, and Williams just needed victory here to achieve the remarkable distinction of holding all four Grand Slam titles at the same time.(n)
